description: This file augments the global Window object and the google namespace for Google Maps API types, providing type definitions and interfaces used in the frontend Vue application.

classes.name: google.maps.Map
classes.description: Represents a Google Map instance, allows setting center and zoom.

classes.name: google.maps.InfoWindow
classes.description: Represents an information window overlay on the map.

classes.name: google.maps.marker.AdvancedMarkerElement
classes.description: Represents a custom advanced marker element on the map.

methods.name: Map.constructor
methods.description: Creates a new Map instance attached to an HTMLElement with options.

methods.name: Map.setCenter
methods.description: Sets the center position of the map.

methods.name: Map.setZoom
methods.description: Sets the zoom level of the map.

methods.name: InfoWindow.constructor
methods.description: Creates a new InfoWindow, optionally with content.

methods.name: InfoWindow.setContent
methods.description: Sets the content of the info window.

methods.name: InfoWindow.open
methods.description: Opens the info window on the specified map, with optional anchor.

methods.name: AdvancedMarkerElement.constructor
methods.description: Creates a new AdvancedMarkerElement with specified options.

methods.name: AdvancedMarkerElement.addListener
methods.description: Adds an event listener to the marker element.

ctags.name: LatLngLiteral
ctags.pattern: /^      type LatLngLiteral = { lat: number; lng: number }$/
